Company Overview of Clayton, Dubilier & Rice, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Clayton, Dubilier & Rice, Inc. is a private equity firm specializing in buyouts, acquisitions, and growth capital financings of mature and underperforming companies. It invests in the manufacturing, healthcare, distribution, services, information technology, chemicals, business services, energy services, new materials, industrial automation, industrial properties and services, and consumer goods sectors. The firm invests in companies based in North America with a focus on the United States and Canada; and Europe with a focus on the United Kingdom, Germany, and Italy. It also identifies and evaluates potential opportunities in France, the Benelux countries, and Asia. It focuses on non-core di...
Clayton, Dubilier & Rice, Inc. is a private equity firm specializing in buyouts, acquisitions, and growth capital financings of mature and underperforming companies. It invests in the manufacturing, healthcare, distribution, services, information technology, chemicals, business services, energy services, new materials, industrial automation, industrial properties and services, and consumer goods sectors. The firm invests in companies based in North America with a focus on the United States and Canada; and Europe with a focus on the United Kingdom, Germany, and Italy. It also identifies and evaluates potential opportunities in France, the Benelux countries, and Asia. It focuses on non-core divisions of large corporations. It makes equity investments between $350 million and $500 million and invests in corporate carve outs, valued at $1 billion to $15 billion. Clayton, Dubilier & Rice, Inc. was established in 1978 and is based in New York, New York with additional offices in George Town, Cayman Islands and London, United Kingdom.
Detailed Description


